Norman Tokar https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Norman_Tokar 0 Norman Tokar (November 25, 1919 – April 6, 1979) was a prolific director and occasionally writer and producer of serial television and feature films, who directed many of the early episodes of Leave it to Beaver, and found his greatest success directing over a dozen films for Walt Disney Productions, spanning the 1950s to the 1970s.
